      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This information is no longer up to date: &quot;The Xms flag has no default value, and Xmx typically has a default value of 256 MB&quot;. It depends if Java considers the machine to be a client or server, and for servers, Xmx can be up to 32GiB. Take a look at <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/vm/gctuning/ergonomics.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/vm/gctuning/&hellip;</a> and <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/vm/gctuning/parallel.html#default_heap_size\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/vm/gctuning/&hellip;</a>"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1468834,
